article.headline: Stetson 76, Lipscomb 66
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Adam Pegg notched his fourth double-double of the season as Stetson completed a season sweep of Atlantic Sun Conference-rival Lipscomb 76-66 Thursday night. Pegg scored 23 points and had 12 rebounds, the latter tying a season high. The senior hit 8 of 12 from the floor and 6 of 10 at the foul line, and he's now scored in double figures in 20 consecutive contests. Chris Perez added 17 points while Aaron Graham had 11 points and Willie Green 11 rebounds for Stetson (11-14, 8-6), which clinched a spot in the A-Sun tournament for the first time since 2008-09. The Hatters downed Lipscomb 85-69 on Jan. 19. The Bisons were coming off a win against Northern Kentucky on Feb. 8 that had snapped a three-game losing streak. Deonte Alexander led Lipscomb with 21 points while Stephen Hurt added 12. The Bisons forced 18 turnovers, including 14 steals.
